Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <Regnar> Listings are less frequent, we're already on some of the biggest exchanges in the world (and Komodo never pays for listings) so there likely aren't listing bumps in price. Community members are definitely encouraged to reach out to their favorite exchanges to see if they will list KMD or Komodo asset chains, but Komodo won't pay for listings and many exchanges charge fees. Though KMD and Komodo asset chains have a far lower risk profile for exchanges as the asset chains and KMD are dPoW protected, which protects exchanges from 51% attacks. Basically when deposits get 2 confirmations it means the transaction was notarized and can't be reversed. (re @PersonalDep: really? well, are there any listings update that will be coming out sooner or later?)

Author: Gateway#3763
Content: [telegram] <Regnar> Exchanges need to calculate the risk of adding altcoins, especially with low hash rates, because they could be the victims of 51% attacks. However dPoW helps reduce this risk so long as the exchange waits for at least 2 confirmations.
